**Version Used**: 16.5 Preview 3

**Steps to Reproduce**:

```csharp
#nullable enable

using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;

public class Base<T> {
  public virtual bool Method([MaybeNullWhen(false)] out T value) => throw null!;
}

public class Derived<T> : Base<T>
  where T : class {
  public override bool Method([NotNullWhen(true)] out T? value) => throw null!;
}
```

**Expected Behavior**:

No diagnostics.

**Actual Behavior**:

warning CS8610: Nullability of reference types in type of parameter 'value' doesn't match overridden member.

_This issue has been moved from [a ticket on Developer Community](https://developercommunity.visualstudio.com/content/idea/918945/analyzer-to-remove-unnecessary-systemconvert.html)._

---
An analyzer should detect cases where type X is passed into the System.Convert.ToX method and suggest removing the Convert invocation.

In the following sample code `System.Convert.ToBoolean` is useless and should be removed.

```
namespace N
{
    public static class C
    {
        public static bool M()
        {
            bool value = true;
            return System.Convert.ToBoolean(value);
        }
    }
}
```

